  <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>

  <p><strong>Effective Date:</strong> April 18, 2025</p>

  <p>This privacy policy explains how the <strong>Fanvue Auto-Reply Assistant</strong> Chrome Extension handles your data and respects your privacy.</p>

  <h2>Information We Collect</h2>
  <p>This extension does <strong>not</strong> collect, transmit, or store any personal data outside your browser. All data used (such as fan messages and replies) is processed locally within your browser session and is not shared with any third parties.</p>

  <h2>Permissions</h2>
  <p>The extension requires the following permissions to function:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>tabs:</strong> To open and close message threads on Fanvue automatically.</li>
    <li><strong>scripting:</strong> To read messages and insert replies into the Fanvue interface.</li>
    <li><strong>storage:</strong> To locally store reply settings and message context to improve response consistency.</li>
    <li><strong>host access to fanvue.com:</strong> To operate on Fanvue messaging pages only.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Data Storage</h2>
  <p>All settings and temporary conversation context are stored using Chrome's local storage. This data never leaves your device and can be cleared at any time by removing the extension or resetting browser data.</p>

  <h2>Third-Party Services</h2>
  <p>This extension does not use third-party analytics, advertising, or data tracking services.</p>

  <h2>Changes to This Policy</h2>
  <p>We may update this privacy policy occasionally. Continued use of the extension after changes are made constitutes acceptance of the updated policy.</p>

  <h2>Contact</h2>
  <p>If you have any questions or concerns about this policy, please contact us at <a href="mailto:fanvueautobot@gmail.com">fanvueautobot@gmail.com</a>.</p>

  <footer>
    &copy; 2025 Fanvue Auto-Reply Assistant. All rights reserved.
  </footer>

